==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Zamang
<hw>Za*mang"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>An immense leguminous tree (<spn>Pithecolobium Saman</spn>) of
Venezuela. Its branches form a hemispherical mass, often one hundred and
eighty feet across. The sweet pulpy pods are used commonly for feeding
cattle. Also called <altname>rain tree</altname>.</def> <rj><au>J. Smith
(Dict. Econ. Plants).</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Zambian</ent>⟦br⟧
